fields.Title: COAST ORB / reeds at lands end
fields.Description: These reeds are in the north, at Land's End. The interactable reeds you can search when Morell tells you to check the phasmid traps. There are traps in these reeds.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Right." It does not look like he t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Right." It does not look like he thinks you're right. "Anyway, that's for the cryptozoologists to figure out now." He adds, for clarity: "*We're* not cryptozoologists -- we're cops."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "Neither does the lieutenant. He jus..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Neither does the lieutenant. He just raises his collar -- it's cold out, as always.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Of course. Noted." He looks at you..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Of course. Noted." He looks at you, incredulously, as you place the trap back in the reeds.

fields.Title: Logic: "No phasmid either -- but still..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No phasmid either -- but still...

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Big surprise." The lieutenant grin..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Big surprise." The lieutenant grins mirthlessly. "Anyway -- one down, three to go."

fields.Title: You: ""Maybe they will still attract some..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Maybe they will still attract something?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Yes. Like a cat, or another teenag..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes. Like a cat, or another teenage psychopath."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Okay. But after that we get back t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay. But after that we get back to our own assignments. We've done a thorough survey of the coast now -- just running around is no longer useful."
fields.Alternate1: "Okay. But after that we get back to our own assignments. There really is *no* explanation for this detour at this point of the investigation."

fields.Title: Trap: Land's End: "The reeds continue to hiss around y..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The reeds continue to hiss around you as you put the empty trap back on the ground. Time to consult the professionals -- Morell and Lena.

fields.Title: You: ""I want to make it clear that I don..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I want to make it clear that I don't *actually* believe the phasmid exists, okay?"
fields.Alternate1: "Again -- I want to make it absolutely *clear* that I don't really believe the phasmid exists, okay?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Always up for a good jog -- otherw..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Always up for a good jog -- otherwise, would I still be *on* this case with *you*?" He smiles and raises his collar. It's windy.

fields.Title: You: "[Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: [Leave.]

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant's gaze follows yours..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant's gaze follows yours and lingers on the reeds, the sand, the water beyond. Then he turns back to you expectantly.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Yup. The next one has a *crab* tra..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yup. The next one has a *crab* trapped in it." He raises his collar -- it's windy. "These are just crab traps, you do realize?"

fields.Title: Trap: Land's End: "A familiar apparatus lies among the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A familiar apparatus lies among the reeds -- another one of Morell's traps, weighed down by stones to keep it in place.

fields.Title: Trap: Land's End: "There's nothing else to do with the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There's nothing else to do with the traps at this time. They're all just lying around, gathering dust and rainwater.

fields.Title: You: ""It'll be in the next one. *Surely*.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "It'll be in the next one. *Surely*."

fields.Title: You: ""You're right. This crypto-research..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You're right. This crypto-research has been stupid."

fields.Title: Trap: Land's End: "No locusts!"
fields.Dialogue Text: No locusts!

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant studies the trap wit..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant studies the trap with you. "Well, the bait worked on *something*. This doesn't mean it was a reed-monster, though. Unless you see one in there? I just see an empty trap..."

fields.Title: Trap: Land's End: "There's a trap in the reeds at your..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There's a trap in the reeds at your feet. Looks like the same one you saw Morell set before -- same mesh, same wiring.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "He purses his lips. "Perhaps our cr..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He purses his lips. "Perhaps our cryptozoologists have competition in the form of an actual entomologist? Or someone else is sabotaging them? I could present more theories, but then I would be taking this on as a case -- which I'm *not*."

fields.Title: Trap: Land's End: "The reeds whisper around the sepulc..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The reeds whisper around the sepulchral trap, as though suddenly filled with fear.
fields.Alternate1: The reeds whisper around the sepulchral trap, as though suddenly filled with fear. Even the snow does not quiet them.
fields.Alternate2: The reeds shudder in the falling rain, whispering. It is as though the sepulchral trap has filled them with some strange, novel fear.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Good, good. We should be courteous..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Good, good. We should be courteous and tell the cryptozoologists that one of their traps was empty, but then we can get back to *our* assignment here."

fields.Title: Authority: "He doesn't want to, but if there is..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He doesn't want to, but if there is one more cryptozoological run-around, he *must* force the investigation back on track. This better be it...

fields.Title: You: ""Bummer it wasn't in here...""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Bummer it wasn't in here..."

fields.Title: Trap: Land's End: "The reeds dance slowly around the e..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The reeds dance slowly around the empty trap. The trap's netting trembles. No insect sounds or movement anywhere.
fields.Alternate1: The reeds dance slowly around the empty trap. The trap's netting trembles, shaking off the snow. No insect sounds or movement anywhere.
fields.Alternate2: The reeds dance slowly around the empty trap. The trap's netting trembles in the cold rain. No insect sounds or movement anywhere.

fields.Title: Trap: Land's End: "The locusts aren't doing all too we..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The locusts aren't doing all too well, but they're still in there. This isn't the *empty* trap. That must have been another one.
fields.Alternate1: The locusts aren't doing all too well, but they're still in there. This isn't the empty trap. That one was by the canal.
fields.Alternate2: The locusts aren't doing all too well, but they're still in there. This isn't the empty trap. That one Morell was setting up, near the cryptozoologists camp.
fields.Alternate3: The locusts aren't doing all too well, but they're still in there. This isn't the empty trap. That one was in Land's End, in the northern tip of this peninsula.

fields.Title: You: ""No need to grin. I'm not *expectin..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No need to grin. I'm not *expecting* to find anything. I'm helping some citizens and getting some fresh air."

fields.Title: Trap: Land's End: "The locusts, dazed from being trans..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The locusts, dazed from being transported, slowly begin to acclimate to their new surroundings.

fields.Title: You: "Release the locusts into the empty..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Release the locusts into the empty trap.

fields.Title: Shivers: "The wind picks up here, near the ca..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The wind picks up here, near the cape's end, surrounding the narrow strip of land from three cardinal directions. It's cold for this time of year.

fields.Title: You: ""Damn, I was hoping it would be in..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Damn, I was hoping it would be in the *first* one."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Good. Now that's done. When can we..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Good. Now that's done. When can we get to our impending apocalypse of a murder investigation?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Of course. Noted." He looks at you..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Of course. Noted." He looks at you, incredulously, as you place the trap back in the reeds.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""No-no. I'm fine. I didn't mean to..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No-no. I'm fine. I didn't mean to complain, it's just..." He's short-winded. The sentence ends there.

fields.Title: You: "[Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: [Leave.]

fields.Title: You: "[Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: [Leave.]

fields.Title: Trap: Land's End: "You've checked all the traps now. T..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You've checked all the traps now. There's nothing else to do with them. The cryptozoologists await your report.

fields.Title: Shivers: "A cold gust of air dries your sweat..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A cold gust of air dries your sweaty face and you look to the dark shadow the Feld building in the distance, drawing you to it. What a strange sensation... Once this is done, should you ask the wind again?

fields.Title: Trap: Land's End: "You set the apparatus back on the g..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You set the apparatus back on the ground, among the reeds.

fields.Title: You: ""I do get the feeling that someone..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I do get the feeling that someone or something may have messed with the trap..."

fields.Title: You: "(Immediately yell.) "It's empty!""
fields.Dialogue Text: (Immediately yell.) "It's empty!"

fields.Title: Trap: Land's End: "This trap is also full of panicked..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This trap is also full of panicked locusts. No sign of any cryptozoological beast inside.

fields.Title: You: "Say nothing, just put the trap down..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Say nothing, just put the trap down.

fields.Title: Trap: Land's End: "The reeds sway in the coastal breez..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The reeds sway in the coastal breeze. They seem to be waiting for something.
fields.Alternate1: The reeds shake sadly in the coastal breeze, weighed down by rain. They seem to be waiting for something.
fields.Alternate2: The reeds shake sadly in the coastal breeze. Snow specks the stalks. Most of it melts quickly, relinquishing form to darkness.
fields.Alternate3: The reeds shake sadly in the coastal breeze. Snow specks the stalks. Most of it melts quickly. The reeds seem to be waiting for something.
fields.Alternate4: The reeds shake sadly in the coastal breeze. They seem to be waiting for something -- some secret concealed in the night's warmthless robe.

fields.Title: You: "Reach for the trap."
fields.Dialogue Text: Reach for the trap.

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "The netting is a little untidy, mes..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The netting is a little untidy, messier than the others. Like someone or something picked up the trap and shook it before dropping it back down on the ground.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I'm just..." he breathes out. "Gla..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm just..." he breathes out. "Glad we haven't found some poor cat trapped in one of these."

fields.Title: Empathy: "Poor things..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Poor things...

fields.Title: You: "Pause and just stand there."
fields.Dialogue Text: Pause and just stand there.

fields.Title: You: "Say nothing, just put the trap down..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Say nothing, just put the trap down.

fields.Title: Trap: Boathouses: "Nothing. No traces of the locusts *..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Nothing. No traces of the locusts *or* the Insulindian phasmid. What happened?

fields.Title: Trap: Land's End: "All the traps are stocked now -- an..."
fields.Dialogue Text: All the traps are stocked now -- and still no sight of the phasmid. Return to Morell and let him know.

fields.Title: You: ""Let's keep going. The next one is..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Let's keep going. The next one is the *lucky* one."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant stretches his back."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant stretches his back.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I'm beginning to feel... somewhat..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm beginning to feel... somewhat sorry for the little guys."

fields.Title: You: "[Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: [Leave.]

fields.Title: You: ""But what if it *was* the phasmid?..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "But what if it *was* the phasmid? What if it ate them and got out?"

fields.Title: You: "Look around."
fields.Dialogue Text: Look around.

fields.Title: You: ""How are you enjoying the cardio, l..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "How are you enjoying the cardio, lieutenant? I'm quite enjoying it myself."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Another empty trap," the lieutenan..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Another empty trap," the lieutenant takes a note -- more out of habit than duty.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I meant no offence, just..." The l..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I meant no offence, just..." The lieutenant doesn't know how to finish the sentence. He looks at you, putting the trap back on the ground.

fields.Title: You: ""Yeah, it probably *wasn't* the pha..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah, it probably *wasn't* the phasmid, but still. Morell needs to know."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "He stops you. "Don't answer that. I..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He stops you. "Don't answer that. It was a rhetorical question."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Surely," he repeats and looks at t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Surely," he repeats and looks at the sea, then at you putting the trap back on the ground. "Anyway, the air is nice and fresh here..."

fields.Title: Trap: Land's End: "This trap's not too hard to spot --..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This trap's not too hard to spot -- once you know what to look for. Keeping it hidden has not been a priority for the cryptozoologist.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Empty as all of them..." he pants...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Empty as all of them..." he pants. "*One* more of these and we're done..." His face is red from the cold sea air. He crouches to catch his breath.

fields.Title: You: "Look closer still."
fields.Dialogue Text: Look closer still.

fields.Title: Trap: Land's End: "Your voice echoes on the coast, car..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Your voice echoes on the coast, carried by a gust of cold wind.

fields.Title: You: ""You're right. But I still need to..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You're right. But I still need to tell the cryptozoologists about this."

fields.Title: Trap: Land's End: "Nothing but locusts in this trap as..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Nothing but locusts in this trap as well. Definitely no cryptozoological monstrosity.

fields.Title: Trap: Land's End: "The trap feels light -- and silent..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The trap feels light -- and silent -- as you pick it up. Something is different here...

fields.Title: You: "Look closer."
fields.Dialogue Text: Look closer.

fields.Title: You: ""I *must* stress that I did not exp..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I *must* stress that I did not expect a cryptozoological monstrosity to be in this trap."
fields.Alternate1: "One more time, I *must* stress that I did not expect a cryptozoological monstrosity to be in this trap."

fields.Title: Trap: Land's End: "Just dead and dying locusts, and th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Just dead and dying locusts, and the slow swaying of surrounding reeds.

fields.Title: Trap: Land's End: "Locusts are crawling around in the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Locusts are crawling around in the trap, confused but uneaten. You see no carnivorous *reed-phasmid* gorging on them.

fields.Title: You: "[Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: [Leave.]

fields.Title: Trap: Land's End: "It takes you a moment, but finally..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It takes you a moment, but finally you spot the last of Morell's traps. This one's partially obscured by the reeds...

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Man, it's lonely doing this alone...."
fields.Dialogue Text: Man, it's lonely doing this alone. The wind seems to howl in a strange manner...

fields.Title: You: "Say nothing, just put the trap down..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Say nothing, just put the trap down.

fields.Title: You: ""You getting tired?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "You getting tired?"

fields.Title: Composure: "They're not really going to get the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: They're not really going to get the chance to get comfortable here.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""We did *sort of* promise to tell t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "We did *sort of* promise to tell them, didn't we..." He seems to regret the fact.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""No you weren't." He looks at the s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No you weren't." He looks at the sea, then you -- laying the trap back down on the ground.

fields.Title: Trap: Land's End: "Nothing has changed about this trap..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Nothing has changed about this trap. You need to check the others.
